The paper discusses interactive visual analytic systems that enable users to discover insights from complex data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for inferring and appending dimensions onto the dataset based on the prior expertise of the user expressed via user interactions, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also discusses semantic interaction techniques that enable systems to learn from the user's interactions and steer the underlying analytic models based on the user's analytical reasoning, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses a technique for manipulating a spatial organization of data, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
